Digital Ambassador
Rwanda Information Society Authority (RISA), Kigali
April 2023 - December 2024
As a Digital Ambassador, I worked with diverse communities in urban and rural
areas to empower individuals with digital skills. This role involved designing and
delivering lessons to people with varying levels of technology familiarity,
emphasizing accessibility and inclusivity.
In urban areas, I focused on digital safety, online government services, and
advanced concepts like digital content creation and social media literacy. In rural
areas, I concentrated on basic skills such as computer usage, internet browsing, and
email management, bridging the digital divide.
I emphasized critical thinking, digital ethics, and responsible technology use,
creating interactive, hands-on learning experiences to boost confidence in using
digital tools effectively.
